{"id": "EUVD-2023-2268", "enisaUuid": "460523c9-a453-378f-b204-729126fde067", "description": "matrix-appservice-irc is a Node.js IRC bridge for Matrix. Prior to version 1.0.1, it was possible to craft an event such that it would leak part of a targeted message event from another bridged room. This required knowing an event ID to target. Version 1.0.1n fixes this issue. As a workaround, set the `matrixHandler.eventCacheSize` config value to `0`. This workaround may impact performance.", "datePublished": "2023-08-04T18:05:43", "dateUpdated": "2024-10-03T18:08:51", "baseScore": 3.5, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:H/PR:L/UI:N/S:C/C:L/I:N/A:N", "references": ["https://github.com/matrix-org/matrix-appservice-irc/security/advisories/GHSA-c7hh-3v6c-fj4q", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2023-38700", "https://github.com/matrix-org/matrix-appservice-irc/commit/8bbd2b69a16cbcbeffdd9b5c973fd89d61498d75", "https://github.com/matrix-org/matrix-appservice-irc", "https://github.com/matrix-org/matrix-appservice-irc/releases/tag/1.0.1"], "aliases": ["CVE-2023-38700", "GHSA-c7hh-3v6c-fj4q"], "assigner": "GitHub_M", "epss": 0.27, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "a27a51e5-152d-337f-9678-2917bb10195e", "product": {"name": "matrix-appservice-irc"}, "product_version": "< 1.0.1"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "74c46b2b-163b-39b5-945b-a5265efb75b5", "vendor": {"name": "matrix-org"}}], "isExploited": false}